From {{inh|ja|ojp|-|sort=ひむかし}}.  Found in the ''{{w|Man'yōshū}}'' dated 759 {{CE}}, but consistently spelled with this single ''kanji'' rather than in ''[[man'yōgana]]'', thus leaving the reading unspecified.<ref name="MYS">{{RQ:Manyoshu|1|48}}, text [http://jti.lib.virginia.edu/japanese/manyoshu/Man1Yos.html#48 here]</ref>

Originally a compound of {{com|ja|sort=ひむかし|日|tr1=hi|t1=[[sun]]||alt2=向か|tr2=muka|t2=[[facing]], [[direction]]|pos2=the {{m|ja|未然形|tr=mizenkei||incomplete form}} of verb {{m|ja|向く|tr=muku}}, “to [[face]] a direction”}}.<ref name="KDJ"/><ref name="DJR"/> The final ''-shi'' is possibly either {{m|ja|風|tr=shi|t=[[wind]], direction|pos=obsolete}} or the suffix {{m|ja|し|tr=-shi}}, the [[adnominal]] form of {{m|ja|き|tr=-ki|pos=classical past tense indicator}}.

